{"to":["sarah.thompson@structuralinnovations.com"],"subject":"Re: Ideas to Strengthen Team Morale","body":"Hi Sarah,

Thank you for raising your concerns about the team’s morale. I appreciate your observations and completely agree that keeping spirits high is crucial as we head into the next phase of the project.

Here are a few steps I’d like to propose:

1. Quick pulse survey next week to gather anonymous feedback on workload, support, and recognition.
2. Weekly 15-minute “wins & shout-outs” at the start of our Tuesday stand-ups so everyone gets a chance to highlight colleagues’ contributions.
3. Schedule optional coffee chats/pair programming rotations to encourage cross-team connection.
4. Review resource allocation for the upcoming milestones to ensure workloads are balanced; I’ll share a draft plan by Friday for your input.

Please let me know if you have additional ideas or if you’d like to co-lead any of the above initiatives. I’m confident that with a few targeted actions we can keep momentum and motivation high.

Thanks again for looking out for the team, and feel free to reach out any time.

Best,
